In a right triangle, the legs measure 5 and 12. Find both acute angles.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 (A) at (0,0);
 (B) at (12,0);
 (C) at (12,5);

 (A) – (B) – (C) – cycle;
 (11.5,0) – (11.5,0.5) – (12,0.5);

 at (A) {$A$};
 at (B) {$B$};
 at (C) {$C$};

 at (6,0) {12};
 at (12,2.5) {5};

 (1.2,0) arc (0:22.6:1.2);
 at (1.8,0.4) {$\alpha$};
tikzpicture
