From a point 50 feet from the base of a flagpole, the angle of 
elevation to the top is $32°$. How tall is the flagpole?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.5]
 % Ground
 (-1,0) – (8,0);

 % Flagpole
 (0,0) – (0,5);
 (0,5) – (0.3,5) – (0.3,4.5);

 % Observer point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (7,0) circle (3pt);

 % Line of sight
 (7,0) – (0,5);

 % Distance
 at (3.5,0) {50 ft};

 % Height
 at (0,2.5) {$h$};

 % Angle
 (5.5,0) arc (180:145:1.5);
 at (5.3,0.5) {$32°$};
tikzpicture
center

A surveyor stands on one bank of a river directly across from a tree 
on the other bank. She walks 100 meters along the bank and finds that 
the angle to the tree is now $62°$. How wide is the river?

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.4]
 % River banks
 ll[blue!10] (-1,-0.5) rectangle (12,0);
 (-1,0) – (12,0);
 (-1,5) – (12,5);

 % Tree
 ll[AtlasSage] (0,5) circle (4pt);
 at (0,5) {Tree};

 % Starting point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (4pt);
 at (0,0) {Start};

 % End point
 ll[AtlasTeal] (10,0) circle (4pt);
 at (10,0) {End};

 % Distance walked
 (0,-1) – (10,-1);
 at (5,-1) {100 m};

 % Line of sight
 (10,0) – (0,5);

 % River width
 (-1.5,0) – (-1.5,5);
 at (-1.5,2.5) {$w$};

 % Angle
 (8,0) arc (180:153:2);
 at (7.5,0.8) {$62°$};
tikzpicture
center
